Date: Wed, 30 Sep 1998 10:25:07 -0500
From: Clyde Markon <docmarkon@worldnet.att.net>
Source: news media

Nepalese Dies after Eating Adulterated Oil in India
-------------------------------------------------------------
30-SEP-98
KATHMANDU (Sept. 30) - One person in Kanchanpur district of
far-western Nepal died of dropsy developed after consuming adulterated
mustard oil in India, the official RSS news agency reported Wednesday.
[The patient returned from New Delhi, India, after developing dropsy
and was admitted to hospital in critical condition. He died on the same
day, RSS said.
Of the other [Nepalese dropsy patients who fell ill in India, three
were still undergoing treatment while three others had been
discharged, the news agency said.
Adulterated mustard oil had claimed more than 50 lives and caused over
2000 cases of dropsy in India by early this month.
[Still no definitive word on whether the toxic ingredient is argemone
or mineral oil - Mod.JW
